---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ - WorkInPrivate" description="Common questions about WorkInPrivate — the simple AI writing program that runs on your own computer. No subscriptions, complete privacy.">

  <!-- FAQ Hero -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-[#F7F9FC]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#4B8BD4] mb-3">Common Questions</div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5 leading-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#5A6474] max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">Everything you need to know about WorkInPrivate, answered in plain English.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto space-y-3">

        <!-- Q1 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            What is WorkInPrivate?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">WorkInPrivate is a simple program that helps you write blog posts, articles, and guides using artificial intelligence. It runs right on your own computer, so your writing stays completely private. There are seven different writing modes to choose from, including blog writing, small business content, healthcare guides, and more.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q2 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            How is this different from ChatGPT?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">ChatGPT runs on the internet and costs $20 every month. WorkInPrivate runs on your own computer for a one-time fee starting at $29. Your writing stays completely private, and you never need an internet connection to use it after the initial setup. Plus, there are no usage limits — write as much as you want.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q3 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            Do I need to be good with computers to use this?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">Not at all! If you can browse the internet and use email, you have all the skills you need. When you open WorkInPrivate for the first time, it walks you through a quick setup — the program handles the hard parts for you. Just type what you want to write about, and it does the rest.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q4 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            What can I write with it?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">WorkInPrivate comes with seven writing modes: Blog Writer (articles for your website), Small Business (marketing and announcements), Finance (money and investing), Healthcare (health guides), Academic (research-style writing), Legal (legal topics and policies), and Tech (software and how-to guides). Each one is specially designed for its subject.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q5 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            Will my computer be able to handle it?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pt-2 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">
            <p class="mb-3">Most computers from the last few years will work just fine. Here's what you'll need:</p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-2 p-0 m-0">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#38A169] mt-1 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span><strong class="text-[#1B3A5C]">Memory:</strong> 8 GB minimum, 16 GB or more is ideal</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#38A169] mt-1 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span><strong class="text-[#1B3A5C]">Hard drive space:</strong> About 5 GB for the program and the AI it downloads during first-time setup</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#38A169] mt-1 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span><strong class="text-[#1B3A5C]">Works on:</strong> Windows 10 or newer, Mac, or Linux</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#38A169] mt-1 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span><strong class="text-[#1B3A5C]">Graphics card:</strong> Not required, but if you have one, articles will be written faster</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q6 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            How do I install it?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">It's really simple — just download the file, save it to your computer, and open it. There's no complicated installation process. The first time you open it, the program walks you through a quick one-time setup where it gets everything ready for you automatically. After that, just open it and start writing.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q7 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            Is my writing really private?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">Yes, completely. Everything happens right on your own computer — your writing is never sent anywhere else. No company collects your work, no algorithm reads your drafts, and no ads follow you around based on what you write. It's just you and your computer. The way it should be.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q8 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            What file types can I save my articles as?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">You can save your articles in several formats: plain text, PDF, Markdown (a simple formatting style popular with bloggers), or HTML (ready to paste into a website). All your finished articles are saved to a folder on your computer, ready to use wherever you need them.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q9 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            Can I use the articles for my business?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">Absolutely. Everything you create with WorkInPrivate is yours to use however you like — publish it on your website, use it for client work, include it in a newsletter, or anything else. There are no restrictions on what you do with your articles.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q10 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            Do I need an internet connection?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">Only for the first-time setup, which takes a few minutes. After that, WorkInPrivate works completely offline — write from a cabin, a coffee shop with spotty Wi-Fi, or your kitchen table. No internet needed. There's an optional web research feature that can look up information online while writing, but it's entirely optional and can be turned off.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q11 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            How do updates work?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">When a new version is available, you can download it from the same place you got the original. Just replace the old file with the new one — your settings and articles are kept safe. Updates are free for the version you purchased.</div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q12 -->
        <details class="border-2 border-[#E2E8F0] rounded-xl overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-5 font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-[#F7F9FC] hover:bg-[#EDF2FA] transition-colors list-none text-base">
            What if I don't like it? Can I get my money back?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#4B8BD4] flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6,9 12,15 18,9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[#5A6474] text-base leading-relaxed bg-[#F7F9FC]">Of course. You have 30 full days to try it out. If it's not right for you, just let us know and we'll refund your money completely. No questions asked, no hassle.</div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4B8BD4 0%, #2E6BB5 100%);">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4 leading-tight">Still Have Questions?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);">We're happy to help. Or if you're ready, give WorkInPrivate a try — there's a 30-day money-back guarantee, so there's nothing to lose.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 px-9 py-5 rounded-xl bg-white text-[#2E6BB5] font-bold text-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all no-underline" style="text-decoration: none; box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);">
          Get Started — From $29
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-center gap-2.5 text-white/80 text-sm font-semibold">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
        30-day money-back guarantee — if you don't love it, get a full refund.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
